  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Grivola's such a cosy hotel to come back to when you've been out exploring the mountains. It has a really unique style and a warm fire to relax by at the end of the day.</p>
<h2>Central location in Cervinia</h2>
<p>Just a short walk away from the Campetto Cretaz lift, this is the ideal hotel for getting out onto those fantastic walking trails as quickly as possible each day. You'll also be right in the centre of town which means you can step out of the hotel and immediately immerse yourself in Cervinia's relaxed atmosphere. Wander around town, try out the bars and cafes and get to know the locals.</p>
<h2>Try out the local food and wine </h2>
<p>The food in this hotel is fantastic, we especially love the steaks. They do the juiciest tomahawk and T-bone steak, well worth a try if this is your type of food. The hotel also has a fantastic selection of wine to choose from with a very knowledgeable maitre-d. This is a fantastic opportunity to try out the wine from the Val D'Aosta and get to know the flavours of the region.</p>
<h2><strong>Great for art lovers</strong></h2>
<p>The Hotel Grivola's the best place to stay if you love being surrounded by creativity. The hotel is the creation of it's owner Gabriel Maquignaz who's also an artist. It's full of eclectic modern art, sculptures and plush furnishings. If you love Gabriel's Modernist style then check out his gallery next door to the hotel, where you can buy his work.</p>
<p><strong>Transfer time:</strong> approx. 2 hours from Milan airport</p>]]></description>
